commit.message:
[NRRPLT-5509] Support recording/playback model and light changes.

This patch adds full support for model and light changes made by the
user/frontend. It properly supports modifications during recording by
waiting for the changes to be properly reflected in Gazebo and then
toggling recording to start/stop and reuse the loading logic. This has
a very small performance hit, but avoid a large number of race conditions
as Gazebo really doesn't like being modified while in playback mode.

After this patch, recording and playback will support all frontend functionality
and default Gazebo behavior in existing experiments. Support for the storage
server implementation and frontend will be completed in the future along with
additional testing.

It also enhances performance of the rosbag player to provide a smoother
playback experience than the "burst" behavior before. A few small formatting
and potential deadlock issues are also resolved during extensive testing.

Change-Id: I93b766600784ea6d408ef21f14daef956b703aef

Create faa_backup.py

Simple convenience script that automates the following processes:

Partial Backup (For fast data analysis and transfer)
A1) Run "faa -p ~/faa_data_directory -t" on data in a experiment day folder
A2) Transfer of folder directory onto mapped network drive (in our case the Synology server)

Full Backup (Go through the full analysis, bag compression, and transfer)
B1) Running "faa -p ~/faa_data/directory -f" on data in a folder
B2) Running of "rosbag compress ~/faa_data/directory/*/*/*.bag" on data for a chosen day
B3) Transfer of chosen folder directory onto mapped network drive while ignoring uncompressed *.orig.bag files

NOTE: Make sure to change the "default_choose_dir" and "default_save_dir" variables
found in the main() function as your backup directory and data directory will
inevitably be different!
